Stick your nose up at street food.
Mauritius is much more rewarding if you have to forage for your own food with deep fried veggies (
gato frire
), and flatbreads (
roti chaud
), stuffed with split peas, curries, chutneys, chilies and pickles, available from street stalls and motorbike vendors across the country. Street food lets you mingle with local people and be a little braver rather than sticking with familiar favourites and hiding in air-conditioned restaurants with English menus.
